			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName> <date>Feb. 11&#47;62</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Noticing in this<lb/> mornings inquirer an<del>d</del> answer to<lb/> your article of this week and think<lb/>ing that I could give you a little<lb/> information on the subject&#44; I thought<lb/> it best to <sic>addres</sic> a few lines to<lb/> you in regard to it.  One of the two<lb/> adults that was baptized in <date>1858</date>&#44;<lb/> I was acquainted with&#44; this young<lb/> Man lived with the <persName>Rev. Dr.<lb/> Newman</persName>&#44; for the space of three<lb/> months at the Doctors expense<lb/> who fitted him out with a<lb/> new suit of clothes and pocket<lb/> money&#59; at the end of which<lb/> time he was baptized&#44; then the<lb/> Doctor gave 100 Dollars and a<lb/> letter to recommendation to the<lb/> firm of <persName>Bunn<add>&#63;</add> Raiquel &#38; Co.</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>who sold about &#36;150 worth of<lb/> goods on Credit after this he<lb/> swindled them all out of their<lb/> money and goods&#44; the name of<lb/> this young man now escapes me<lb/> but I think if it is necessary<lb/> I can ascertain it.  <sic>Hopeing</sic> these<lb/> few lines may be a source of<lb/> information to you in order to<lb/> carry on your controversy I<lb/> remain yours respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Louis Potsdamer</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>331 Market St.</placeName></p>
		</body>
